The paper discusses a system for database query performance problem determination, which falls under the category of database systems (cs.DB). The system uses a knowledge base and semantic web technology to analyze query execution plans, which involves artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) techniques. The system also involves software engineering (cs.SE) principles for transforming QEPs into RDF graphs and creating a user interface for searching and displaying results. Finally, the system involves information retrieval (cs.IR) techniques for matching user-defined patterns to QEPs and retrieving relevant recommendations from the knowledge base.
